cs.PL, cs.OS, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses WebAssembly as a compilation target for languages like C and C++, which falls under the domain of programming languages. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems): The paper introduces Browsix-Wasm, an extension to Browsix that enables running Unix applications in the browser environment, which involves operating system concepts. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper evaluates the performance of WebAssembly vs. native code, which involves analyzing the underlying architecture of the systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper identifies the causes of performance degradation in WebAssembly, which involves software engineering concepts. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper uses the SPEC CPU suite of benchmarks to evaluate the performance of WebAssembly, which involves distributed and parallel computing concepts.
